Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_visible_nets(25.10)                                set_visible_nets(25.10)

Name
       set_visible_nets - Displays only the specified nets and hides all other
       nets

Syntax
       set_visible_nets

       [-help]

       {<nets> | -all}

       Displays only the specified nets and hides all other nets.

       To display all nets, specify the -all parameter.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each set_visible_nets parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man set_visible_nets

       -all   Displays all nets.

       <nets> Displays  only  the specified nets and hides all other nets. You
              can specify multiple net names.

Examples
              * The following command hides all nets except the specified net:

                set_visible_nets inst1/lower/net_1

Related Information
              * get_visible_nets

